## Herring die-off{.fl background-image="images/robert2013.jpg"}

Kolgrafafj√∂r√∞ur `(KF)` in winter 2012/13

:::: {.columns}

::: {.column .box width="50%"}

- In the winter of 2012, a significant **hypoxic** event occurred, leading to the death of **55,000 tonnes** of **herring**.
- The dead herring sank to the bottom of the fjord, creating a **layer** of **organic** material.
-   This layer of decomposing herring consumed the remaining oxygen, creating **anoxic** conditions at the bottom of the fjord.
-   These dramatic changes to the ecosystem sparked our interest and led us to investigate the impact on the benthic community.

:::



::::

