## Understanding Hypoxia


-   Hypoxia refers to a state in which oxygen levels in a particular environment are significantly reduced.
-   Hypoxic conditions can be temporary or permanent, depending on the nature of the water body and the extent of the nutrient input.
-   In the specific case of the Kolgrafafj√∂r√∞ur fjord, the presence of 200,000 tonnes of herring in a small, secluded fjord led to a rapid depletion of oxygen, causing a hypoxic event. When these herring died and sank to the bottom, their decomposition further consumed the remaining oxygen, leading to anoxic conditions on the seafloor.


Image: Consider including a diagram illustrating the process of eutrophication leading to hypoxia, or an image showing the impact of hypoxia on aquatic life.


